---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import LessonShell from "../../components/LessonShell.astro";
import ProductIcon from "../../components/ProductIcon.astro";
import { LESSONS } from "../../data/curriculum";

const lesson = LESSONS.find((l) => l.id === "capabilities")!;

const tiers = [
  {
    kind: "chat" as const,
    title: "Ship today, in chat",
    items: ["Writing & email", "Analysis of PDFs / CSVs", "Plans & itineraries", "One-page mini-apps", "Diagrams"],
  },
  {
    kind: "code" as const,
    title: "Build this week",
    items: ["A personal CLI", "Small websites", "Chrome extensions", "Slack / Discord bots", "Internal dashboards"],
  },
  {
    kind: "agents" as const,
    title: "Ship in production",
    items: ["Customer-facing apps", "Agent workflows", "Document pipelines", "Embedded copilots"],
  },
];
---

<Layout title={`${lesson.title} · Learn Claude`}>
  <main>
    <LessonShell lesson={lesson} hero="claude">
      <p>Three ambition levels. Pick the row that matches what you want.</p>

      <div class="cap-grid">
        {tiers.map((t) => (
          <div class="cap-card">
            <ProductIcon kind={t.kind} size={40} />
            <h3>{t.title}</h3>
            <ul>{t.items.map((i) => <li>{i}</li>)}</ul>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <h2>Which product, when?</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Situation</th><th>Open</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>In a project folder, touching code</td><td><strong>Claude Code</strong></td></tr>
          <tr><td>Long chores against a repo</td><td><strong>Cowork</strong></td></tr>
          <tr><td>Needs to look visual</td><td><strong>Design</strong></td></tr>
          <tr><td>Phone / tablet / someone else's laptop</td><td><strong>Claude.ai</strong></td></tr>
          <tr><td>Drop in a PDF or screenshot</td><td><strong>Claude.ai</strong></td></tr>
          <tr><td>A non-developer needs to use it</td><td><strong>Claude.ai</strong></td></tr>
          <tr><td>Persistent assistant with knowledge files</td><td><strong>Claude.ai</strong> (Projects)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Background daemon with memory</td><td><strong>Hermes / OpenClaw</strong></td></tr>
          <tr><td>Embedding in your own product</td><td><strong>Claude API</strong></td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <p style="color: var(--ink-soft); font-size: 0.92rem;">
        If you have a terminal open in the right folder, Claude Code wins most of the time. The other products
        cover the cases where you don't — or where the work isn't about code.
      </p>
    </LessonShell>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .cap-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 0.6rem;
    margin: 1rem 0 1.6rem;
  }
  .cap-card {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1rem 0.95rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }
  .cap-card h3 { margin: 0.2rem 0 0.15rem; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .cap-card ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1rem; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--ink-soft); }
  .cap-card li { margin: 0.1rem 0; }
  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .cap-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
